---
name: Offline Playback
description: IndexedDB caching, SW app-shell fallback, single-audio guard, offline-first lyrics + karaoke
type: feature
---
Offline cache (IndexedDB store `cachedAudio`) bundles per track:
- audioBlob (MP3)
- syncedLyrics, plainLyrics
- karaokeData, karaokeEnabled, lyricsSpeed, bounceIntensity

Service Worker (vite-plugin-pwa, autoUpdate):
- Precaches js/css/html/ico/png/svg/webp/woff2.
- `navigateFallback: /index.html` so the app shell loads fully offline.
- Same-origin static assets → CacheFirst (`static-assets`).
- Cross-origin GET (Supabase, lyrics.ovh) → NetworkFirst with 4s timeout, cache fallback (`api-cache`).
- Do NOT use a single catch-all `^https://.*` NetworkFirst — it breaks navigation offline.

Player rules:
- Single active audio element via `loadTokenRef` + `stopCurrentSource()` in PlayerContext.
- Audio resolution priority: IndexedDB cached blob > local audioFiles store > remote `audio_url` (online only, 4s/8s timeouts) > YouTube IFrame fallback.

Lyrics + karaoke offline:
- LyricsView always tries `getCachedLyrics` + `getCachedKaraoke` FIRST.
- When offline AND cache hit, skip all Supabase/lyrics.ovh fetches.
- Online path wraps `fetchMergedSongRecord` and `fetchSyncedLyrics` in 4s/6s timeouts.
- Cached karaoke restores: words, early_appearance, mobile_char_limit, lyrics_speed, bounce_intensity.

Lossless badge: shown below the playback control row, 12px capitalised "Lossless" (NOT uppercase) with `Disc3` icon — same on desktop, mobile, and lyrics view.
